MKDoc::Control_List - Complex Set of Rules Abstraction
======================================================

Access Control List is a security model which allows much finer control of
resources than other traditional permission systems such as Unix.

MKDoc::Control_List is a generalization of the concept of Access Control Lists.
Using this module, you can define represent arbitrarily complex rules in a
configuration file in a manageable way.

MKDoc::Control_List has the following uses in MKDoc:

* Access Control (Authorization)
* Caching Policy


INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

  perl Makefile.PL
  make
  make test
  make install

Or better, use CPAN.pm


DEPENDENCIES

  none.


